Calcluate the log and plot the scatter plot again with saleprice¶

In [14]:
for feature in continuous_feature:
    data=df.copy()
    
    if 0 in data[feature].unique():
        pass
    else:
        data[feature]=np.log(data[feature])
        data['SalePrice']=np.log(data['SalePrice'])
        plt.scatter(data[feature],data['SalePrice'])
        plt.xlabel(feature)
        plt.ylabel('SalePrice')
        plt.title(feature)
        plt.show()

Split the dataset into two part train and test, applied Minmaxscaler and Linear Regression. Cross check accuracy with Ridge Regression¶
